    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/factor/relevance-validation-activities",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "This factor assesses the degree to which the validation activities (bench tests) are representative of the clinical use environment. For ASTM F1717 testing, the standard itself is the regulatory reference condition — the COU is defined as predicting F1717 test outcomes, not in vivo spinal loading. Therefore the validation activity IS the COU, and a separate relevance assessment of the validation activity relative to itself is circular and not meaningful. The factor is scoped out on this basis, consistent with ASME V&V 40 §6.4 guidance that relevance assessment applies when validation is performed in a surrogate environment distinct from the COU; here no such distinction exists."
    }
